{"key":"post-10806821","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10806821</id>\n<content>Technically, the substrate doesn't soak up any water when you dunk.&amp;nbsp; The mycelium does, and that's why it takes 24 hours.&amp;nbsp; An uncolonized substrate would be fully hydrated in ten seconds or less if submerged.&amp;nbsp; Since the substrate has been fully colonized with mushroom mycelium, you have to hydrate the individual cells via osmosis, and that takes plenty of time.&amp;nbsp; Waterlogging happens when someone puts a cake or other bulk substrate directly on the perlite and the mycelium continues to absorb water until it's saturated.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10807163</next>\n<prev>10806750</prev>\n<first>10806691</first>\n<last>10816565</last>\n<when>1249515378</when>\n<utime>08/06/09 02:36 AM</utime>\n</post>"}